Privacy Policy

Last Updated: [Date]

1. IntroductionWelcome to GEINOTECH. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our studying platform.

2. Information We CollectWe collect the following types of information:

Account Information: When you sign up or sign in, including through Google Sign-In, we collect your name, email address, and any other relevant details.

User Submissions: When you provide suggestions (pros, cons, or possible improvements), we collect the content of your submission.

Cookies and Tracking Data: We use cookies and similar technologies to improve user experience and analyze site traffic.

3. How We Use Your InformationWe use your data to:

Provide and improve our platform.

Respond to user feedback and suggestions.

Ensure security and prevent fraud.

Comply with legal obligations.

4. Third-Party ServicesWe use Google Sign-In for authentication. Your data is subject to Google's Privacy Policy. We may also use third-party analytics tools to track and analyze website performance.

5. Data ProtectionWe implement security measures to protect your personal data. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

6. Your RightsDepending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including access, correction, and deletion.

7. Changes to This PolicyWe may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on our website.

8. Contact UsIf you have questions, contact us at [Your Contact Email].

Cookies Policy

1. What Are Cookies?Cookies are small text files stored on your device to enhance your browsing experience.

2. How We Use CookiesWe use cookies to:

Improve website functionality.

Analyze traffic and user behavior.

Enable authentication via Google Sign-In.

3. Managing CookiesYou can control cookie settings in your browser. Disabling cookies may affect your experience on our site.

4. Changes to This PolicyWe may update this Cookies Policy from time to time.

5. Contact UsFor questions, contact us at [Your Contact Email].
